<i>That was the biggest loss
we've seen today.</i>

01:22:10.489 --> 01:22:12.252
<i>We're now in historic territory.</i>

01:22:12.357 --> 01:22:14.791
<i>Investors are getting
their heads handed to them</i>

01:22:14.893 --> 01:22:17.919
<i>as another US banking institution
nears collapse.</i>

01:22:18.030 --> 01:22:20.828
<i>The President's Working Group
is going into emergency meetings</i>

01:22:20.933 --> 01:22:23.993
<i>with the Secretary of the Treasury
and the Federal Reserve Board.</i>

01:22:32.377 --> 01:22:35.869
The President's Chief of Staff
is calling back in an hour.

01:22:35.981 --> 01:22:37.278
He's with the President.

01:22:37.382 --> 01:22:40.909
And he's going to want to know
what I think we should do.

01:22:41.853 --> 01:22:44.117
This isn't Keller Zabel, Bill.

01:22:46.124 --> 01:22:48.251
This is too big to fail.

01:22:48.427 --> 01:22:51.590
- This is just an insane situation.
- This is now.

01:22:51.697 --> 01:22:54.723
There's about 70-plus trillion out there
in credit default swaps

01:22:54.833 --> 01:22:56.164
held by roughly 17 banks.

01:22:56.268 --> 01:22:58.429
