<i>And we are talking on the S&P 500</i>

01:27:42.120 --> 01:27:44.850
<i>a loss of almost eight percent in one day,</i>

01:27:44.956 --> 01:27:47.481
<i>surpassing September 17th, 2001.</i>

01:27:47.592 --> 01:27:50.925
<i>That's the day markets opened
after the attacks of 9/11.</i>

01:27:51.029 --> 01:27:52.462
<i>...last night on Wall Street</i>

01:27:52.564 --> 01:27:55.465
<i>and swept through
Japan, China, India and Europe</i>

01:27:55.567 --> 01:27:59.697
<i>after one of the worst days
on global stock markets in modern times.</i>

01:28:44.349 --> 01:28:46.180
They said your office.

01:28:48.119 --> 01:28:51.350
It's too depressing today.
This is my other office.

01:28:52.924 --> 01:28:55.119
This might be dangerous.
Think you can keep up?

01:28:55.327 --> 01:28:57.386
World's crashing anyway.
We'll see, right?

01:30:20.612 --> 01:30:22.375
That's not bad, Jake.

01:30:23.148 --> 01:30:25.480
Though I think they might have
given you the faster bike.

01:30:25.583 --> 01:30:27.676
I'm sure that's what it was.

01:30:29.187 --> 01:30:30.415
You know,

01:30:31.122 --> 01:30:32.851
I've always believed
that a man should have,

01:30:32.957 --> 01:30:37.394
at one time or another in his life,
both a mentor and a protg.

01:30:37.862 --> 01:30:38.886
Who's yours?

01:30:38.997 --> 01:30:41.022
The man who brought me
into Churchill Schwartz.

01:30:41.132 --> 01:30:45.535
Bill Clark at Treasury.
He's been a good friend to us during this crisis.

01:30:46.271 --> 01:30:48.739
You got the makings of a leader, Jake.

01:30:48.840 --> 01:30:52.207
I just want you to know,
there's no hard feelings on this.

01:30:52.977 --> 01:30:54.672
No one's going to lose.

01:30:54.779 --> 01:30:57.111
With Clark in,
I think we're in good shape.

01:30:57.215 --> 01:30:58.944
You got a great future.

01:30:59.050 --> 01:31:00.745
I don't understand.

01:31:01.252 --> 01:31:03.311
Didn't you read this morning's
capital breakdown?

01:31:03.421 --> 01:31:06.686
No, I came right up to the roof.
Why? What happened?

01:31:08.326 --> 01:31:14.162
Look, the Chinese money,
it's going to Babaco Solar.

01:31:16.267 --> 01:31:18.201
- What?
- We took another look

01:31:18.303 --> 01:31:20.999
and we just don't think United Fusion
is ever gonna achieve what they claim.

01:31:21.106 --> 01:31:23.438
Babaco needs this money to build
these three fabrications...

01:31:23.541 --> 01:31:24.803
You might as well
just burn the money, Bretton.

01:31:24.909 --> 01:31:27.241
You told me, I told Dr. Masters.
He's expecting it.

01:31:27.345 --> 01:31:29.370
The decision's been made.

01:31:29.481 --> 01:31:31.472
Unless you want it to die.

01:31:32.650 --> 01:31:37.144
Of course. Seawater is in a lot more supply
than crude. Right, Bretton?

01:31:37.255 --> 01:31:40.418
- You an idealist or a capitalist, Jacob?
- I'm a realist.

01:31:41.259 --> 01:31:43.284
You're a real piece of work, Bretton.

01:31:43.394 --> 01:31:45.555
You're giving the money to Babaco
because it's a hustle.

01:31:45.663 --> 01:31:48.530
It's all inside. That's why
your oil companies are safe, right?

01:31:48.633 --> 01:31:53.593
The mentor-protg relationship
is not emotional over anything.

01:31:54.606 --> 01:31:57.200
I thought you might be a good addition
to the Churchill Schwartz team.

01:31:57.308 --> 01:31:58.900
- Am I mistaken?
- Let me tell you something, Bretton.

01:31:59.010 --> 01:32:02.275
You are not my mentor. Lou Zabel was.
And whether you admit it or not,

01:32:02.514 --> 01:32:05.449
your raid destroyed Zabel
and forced him to suicide.

01:32:05.550 --> 01:32:09.145
So you may talk about moral hazard.
You are the moral hazard.

01:32:09.621 --> 01:32:13.580
You are the worst kind of toxic debt
this system's polluted with.

01:32:15.426 --> 01:32:17.656
- Is this a threat?
- Absolutely.

01:32:25.870 --> 01:32:27.861
This is so disappointing.

01:32:28.806 --> 01:32:31.274
I really saw so much in you, Jacob.

01:32:32.944 --> 01:32:37.677
You should look in the mirror first.
See yourself. It might scare you, Bretton.

01:32:42.353 --> 01:32:44.446
Consider the motorcycle
part of your severance.

01:32:44.556 --> 01:32:46.183
Fuck you, Bretton!

01:32:52.997 --> 01:32:54.362
- Here you are.
- Thanks a lot.

01:32:54.465 --> 01:32:56.660
- Hi. For Elise.
- "For Elise."

01:32:56.768 --> 01:32:59.635
- And can I ask you a question, Mr. Gekko?
- Certainly, Elise.

01:32:59.737 --> 01:33:02.069
What exactly is "moral hazard"?

01:33:02.173 --> 01:33:04.300
- He screwed me.
- Excuse me?

01:33:05.476 --> 01:33:06.534
Shocker.

01:33:06.644 --> 01:33:09.841
He saw that fusion was actually possible,
so he killed it.

01:33:09.948 --> 01:33:12.007
Well, that's a little far-fetched.

01:33:12.116 --> 01:33:14.516
But then, these days,
anything is possible.

01:33:14.619 --> 01:33:16.382
Well, I quit, Gordon.

01:33:17.121 --> 01:33:21.023
That's really going to help.
I'll see you outside in 15 minutes.

01:33:21.226 --> 01:33:24.218
Moral hazard, that's when somebody

01:33:24.329 --> 01:33:27.355
takes your money
and is not responsible for it.

01:33:28.433 --> 01:33:32.301
This guy James,
he must walk between raindrops.

01:33:32.403 --> 01:33:34.963
He's a monkey dancing on a razorblade.

01:33:35.940 --> 01:33:40.502
Not only did he start the rumors at Zabel
to get your bank for peanuts,

01:33:40.612 --> 01:33:43.274
the guy was trading for his own account
in this Locust Fund.

01:33:43.381 --> 01:33:44.678
- He was?
- He was.

01:33:44.816 --> 01:33:48.650
And he was betting against the market
that he was making.

01:33:48.753 --> 01:33:52.553
But the kicker is, so was his firm.

01:33:52.657 --> 01:33:55.091
Churchill Schwartz was shorting sub-primes?

01:33:55.193 --> 01:33:58.060
Yeah, for the last two years
they've been hedging.

01:33:58.162 --> 01:34:01.893
Not just sub-primes.
Primes, indexes, the whole thing.

01:34:03.501 --> 01:34:07.733
But they knew this home loan fantasy
was going to collapse the market.

01:34:08.806 --> 01:34:10.797
And when they did, they got the Feds

01:34:10.908 --> 01:34:15.811
to bail out their bad insurance swaps,
a 100 cents on the dollar.

01:34:16.014 --> 01:34:19.541
I mean, talk about an evil empire.
This puts me to shame.

01:34:19.817 --> 01:34:22.718
And I'm small-time
compared to these crooks.

01:34:24.522 --> 01:34:27.821
The system is insolvent
if no one knows what to do next,

01:34:27.925 --> 01:34:31.326
except repeat the insanity
till the next bubble blows.

01:34:32.463 --> 01:34:34.761
That'll be the one.
The big one.

01:34:35.833 --> 01:34:38.825
The tipping point, just like the tulip.

01:34:38.936 --> 01:34:42.736
We could still go after James on this.
Just bring it all out.

01:34:42.840 --> 01:34:44.569
Easy, Trigger.

01:34:44.676 --> 01:34:48.134
Media is not going to get in the way
of Churchill or the government.

01:34:48.246 --> 01:34:51.010
They want their profits
just like the rest of us.

01:34:51.115 --> 01:34:53.174
It's unethical, but it's not illegal.

01:34:53.284 --> 01:34:56.742
When everyone's running for the lifeboats,
who's going to care?

01:34:56.854 --> 01:34:59.379
Maybe some little leftist website?

01:34:59.490 --> 01:35:01.151
Your daughter will run it.
It'll get some play.

01:35:06.631 --> 01:35:10.863
Look, Bretton is not an enemy
a kid like you wants to have for life.

01:35:10.968 --> 01:35:12.094
Just get out of this racket.

01:35:12.770 --> 01:35:15.898
Settle down with Winnie.
Live a happy life somewhere.

01:35:16.007 --> 01:35:19.033
- What?
- Well, you know, she's got enough money.

01:35:19.143 --> 01:35:21.134
- What do you mean?
- You're smart.

01:35:21.245 --> 01:35:22.769
You'll come up with another way
to slice bread.

01:35:22.880 --> 01:35:25.440
- What money?
- My money.

01:35:27.151 --> 01:35:29.415
Stop playing it dumb, will you, Jake?
I know you know.

01:35:29.520 --> 01:35:30.817
Know what?

01:35:32.223 --> 01:35:33.918
Are you telling me
that you're not the only one

01:35:34.058 --> 01:35:36.652
in this relationship keeping a secret?

01:35:38.863 --> 01:35:40.490
Hold on a second.
What money, Gordon?

01:35:42.333 --> 01:35:44.699
- Switzerland.
- How much?

01:35:46.671 --> 01:35:49.504
It's close to $100 million by now.

01:35:54.078 --> 01:35:56.308
What do you say we split a cab?

01:36:02.587 --> 01:36:06.887
I set it up as a Swiss account in the '80s
before all the trouble.

01:36:06.991 --> 01:36:08.015
Hey, chief.

01:36:08.259 --> 01:36:10.693
Look, I'll pay you extra.
Just slow down.

01:36:10.795 --> 01:36:12.023
Can you... Can you...

01:36:12.130 --> 01:36:16.396
When she was 18, I told her she would come
into it all when she turned 25.

01:36:17.635 --> 01:36:20.399
And she agreed to stake me
when I got out.

01:36:21.406 --> 01:36:24.842
Then Rudy died, and she reneged.

01:36:25.143 --> 01:36:26.508
She never visited me again.

01:36:27.545 --> 01:36:29.410
She told me she had a small trust

01:36:29.514 --> 01:36:31.277
from you and her mom,
but she didn't care anything about it.

01:36:31.382 --> 01:36:33.509
She was going to give it to charity
when she was 25.

01:36:33.618 --> 01:36:35.882
Well, it's easy for her to say.
She never earned it.

01:36:37.388 --> 01:36:40.448
And now you want it
for your fusion delusion.

01:36:40.558 --> 01:36:44.119
But it's a trust. I mean, she couldn't break
into it before she was 25 anyway.

01:36:44.228 --> 01:36:47.254
Are you as dumb as you sound?
Anything can be revoked.

01:36:47.365 --> 01:36:51.563
They don't got trusts in Switzerland.
It's an account, that's all.

01:36:52.069 --> 01:36:54.867
I know the bank well.
They'll work with me.

01:36:55.573 --> 01:36:58.303
But you still need her signature, of course.

01:36:59.644 --> 01:37:04.013
When it comes to money, sport,
your eyes suddenly shine, just like mine.

01:37:06.851 --> 01:37:08.910
Great! Saved another life, huh?

01:37:09.821 --> 01:37:10.947
Asshole!

01:37:11.055 --> 01:37:12.989
Are you crazy?
You want to die? Huh?

01:37:17.795 --> 01:37:18.921
How do we do this?

01:37:21.566 --> 01:37:25.263
She goes with you to Switzerland,
she signs the account over to your control,

01:37:25.369 --> 01:37:28.202
then you give me the money
and I'll get it to the States for you.

01:37:29.006 --> 01:37:30.564
You mean launder it?

01:37:31.108 --> 01:37:33.338
Look, pal, you want the IRS on Winnie?

01:37:33.444 --> 01:37:37.505
Because you damn well know
she is complicit and seriously liable.

01:37:37.615 --> 01:37:39.082
All right? You want the money?

01:37:57.201 --> 01:37:58.463
- Hi. How are you?
- Hi.

01:37:58.569 --> 01:38:02.369
- Can I talk to you for a second?
- Yeah. I'll be back in a sec.

01:38:04.876 --> 01:38:07.777
Why didn't you tell me
about the $100 million?

01:38:11.215 --> 01:38:15.675
How did you find...
How did you find out in the first place?

01:38:15.987 --> 01:38:17.420
Did you talk to my father?

01:38:17.522 --> 01:38:19.717
I found out because Churchill Schwartz's
international trading desk

01:38:19.824 --> 01:38:21.451
handles some of the money,
and your name came up,

01:38:21.559 --> 01:38:22.651
along with Gordon Gekko.

01:38:22.760 --> 01:38:26.890
I never considered it mine.
I was 14. I was a minor when he set it up.

01:38:26.998 --> 01:38:28.090
Yeah, but you didn't do anything
with the money

01:38:28.199 --> 01:38:29.223
when you turned into a major, did you?

01:38:29.333 --> 01:38:31.233
- I was going to give it to charity.
- Really?

01:38:31.335 --> 01:38:33.826
What were you gonna do,
launder the money yourself, Winnie?

01:38:33.938 --> 01:38:37.203
- What was your plan?
- I didn't think about it.

01:38:37.308 --> 01:38:39.242
- You didn't think about it?
- It was my father's money.

01:38:39.343 --> 01:38:41.140
- You know how he got it.
- No, you're wrong. It's your money.

01:38:41.245 --> 01:38:43.907
It's $100 million of your money.

01:38:44.015 --> 01:38:45.482
Do you know what that means?

01:38:46.017 --> 01:38:49.851
That's five years in jail. You're gonna
get busted with him for tax fraud.

01:38:49.954 --> 01:38:51.888
This is serious, Winnie.

01:38:59.297 --> 01:39:02.164
You could do something good
with this money.

01:39:03.267 --> 01:39:05.098
This is more than just charity, Winn.

01:39:07.171 --> 01:39:10.402
You might want to wipe some of the drool
off your face, Jake.

01:39:10.942 --> 01:39:13.103
Winnie, if it wasn't important,
I'd totally understand, but it is.

01:39:13.210 --> 01:39:15.075
You know that fusion just might work.

01:39:15.179 --> 01:39:17.272
I know it sounds like <i>Star Wars,</i> love,

01:39:17.381 --> 01:39:19.872
but if it weren't for crazy people
who thought these crazy things,

01:39:19.984 --> 01:39:22.953
then where would we be in this world?
Nowhere.

01:39:23.521 --> 01:39:24.579
Huh?

01:39:25.056 --> 01:39:28.253
Winnie, Dr. Masters is a genius.
He's a pioneer.

01:39:28.359 --> 01:39:30.156
They might just solve this thing.
It could change the world.

01:39:30.261 --> 01:39:32.422
Yeah, okay.
Is this about changing the world or making money?

01:39:32.530 --> 01:39:34.088
Because you come into my office,
pitching to me.

01:39:34.198 --> 01:39:35.495
You sound like a Wall Street guy.

01:39:35.600 --> 01:39:38.569
Hold on for a second!
I am a Wall Street guy.

01:39:38.669 --> 01:39:39.829
I am and I'm good at this.

01:39:39.937 --> 01:39:42.838
And I believe in this.
And you know that I do.

01:39:42.940 --> 01:39:45.204
What do you wanna do, just report
the news for the rest of your life

01:39:45.309 --> 01:39:47.004
or do you want to make the news?
This is your opportunity.

01:39:47.111 --> 01:39:49.375
It's your chance to shine.

01:39:49.480 --> 01:39:51.311
To be Captain America.

01:39:56.153 --> 01:39:59.816
This is the most charitable
you could ever be in your life!

01:40:06.530 --> 01:40:08.691
You honestly believe in this?

01:40:10.201 --> 01:40:13.796
Let's say I could... Let's say I could get
the money now, hypothetically, right?

01:40:13.904 --> 01:40:14.962
Not that you care about the money.

01:40:15.072 --> 01:40:16.334
But let's say I could take out
a loan against it,

01:40:16.440 --> 01:40:19.102
minimize your risk as much as possible.

01:40:20.144 --> 01:40:22.476
Would you do this for me, Winn?

01:40:24.882 --> 01:40:26.850
Would you do this for me?

01:40:53.177 --> 01:40:55.805
Very well, Miss Gekko.
We will have your father co-sign

01:40:55.913 --> 01:40:58.040
and we will see to it
that the funds are transferred.

01:40:58.149 --> 01:40:59.980
- Thank you.
- <i>Danke schon,</i> Miss Gekko.

01:41:00.418 --> 01:41:01.646
- Mr. Moore.
- Yes?

01:41:01.752 --> 01:41:05.347
Mr. Gekko asked that you call him in New York
as soon as this meeting is over.

01:41:05.456 --> 01:41:06.753
Thank you.

01:41:08.459 --> 01:41:10.689
So I'll take care of the rest of this.
You go back to the hotel.

01:41:10.795 --> 01:41:11.989
- All right.
- I just got the confirmation.

01:41:12.096 --> 01:41:13.563
We're on the direct flight to New York
in the morning.

01:41:13.664 --> 01:41:14.790
Great.

01:41:15.833 --> 01:41:17.130
- Great news on the loft.
- Oh, yeah?

01:41:17.234 --> 01:41:20.169
Yeah, I got a buyer.
So one less thing in our lives, right?

01:41:20.271 --> 01:41:22.739
- I kind of like the feeling.
- Yeah, so do I.

01:41:22.840 --> 01:41:25.104
- I'll see you over there.
- Okay.

01:41:33.851 --> 01:41:37.150
Hey, anyone can figure out life
when you're looking back on it.

01:41:37.254 --> 01:41:40.655
But we got to live it going forward.
Right, Jakie?

01:41:41.926 --> 01:41:45.384
Besides, four-and-a-half is great
in this market.

01:41:45.496 --> 01:41:48.329
Yeah, except I owe six to the bank.
When do I have to be out of here?

01:41:48.432 --> 01:41:50.559
You got three months more.

01:41:50.668 --> 01:41:54.229
By the way,
I had to throw in the furniture.

01:41:54.805 --> 01:41:56.602
What there was of it.

01:41:57.975 --> 01:42:00.068
Did you want me to have a yard sale
here for you?

01:42:01.312 --> 01:42:03.246
Here. Take it.
Here's your pen.

01:42:11.922 --> 01:42:14.322
- Jake...
- Dolores was just leaving.

01:42:15.226 --> 01:42:16.318
Oh.

01:42:20.397 --> 01:42:24.731
Hello to you, too, honey.
Don't forget. Three months, honey.

01:42:24.835 --> 01:42:25.961
Mmm-hmm.

01:42:30.207 --> 01:42:33.608
- Bastards changed the locks.
- You weren't servicing the loans, Ma.

01:42:33.711 --> 01:42:36.703
Well, they lied to me. They told me
they were going to give me more time.

01:42:36.814 --> 01:42:39.009
Well, they're not, okay?
They're panicking. Everyone is panicking.

01:42:39.116 --> 01:42:41.710
They're gonna throw it in the market
and take what they can get for it, Ma.

01:42:41.819 --> 01:42:43.946
But it's not even finished yet.

01:42:44.054 --> 01:42:46.716
And that's not all. Look.

01:42:46.824 --> 01:42:48.553
It's the other properties, Mom.

01:42:48.659 --> 01:42:50.991
No, but they said they were gonna give me
a little more time.

01:42:51.095 --> 01:42:52.653
And all I need is a 110 grand,

01:42:52.763 --> 01:42:55.857
and then that way,
I can keep all three properties in play.

01:42:55.966 --> 01:42:57.695
- I know you have it, Jake.
- I don't have it, Mom.

01:42:57.802 --> 01:42:59.235
- You have it, Jacob.
- I don't have it,

01:42:59.336 --> 01:43:00.894
and I wouldn't give it to you
if I did have it.

01:43:01.705 --> 01:43:04.071
- What am I supposed to do?
- You know what moral hazard is, Ma?

01:43:04.175 --> 01:43:05.267
- You know what that means?
- No.

01:43:05.376 --> 01:43:06.934
It means that once you get bailed out,
what's to stop you

01:43:07.044 --> 01:43:09.410
- from taking another shot?
- But I...

01:43:09.513 --> 01:43:11.538
I'm in trouble, Mom.
I am in trouble right now.

01:43:11.649 --> 01:43:14.049
I'm taking a huge hit on the loft,
I just sold my bike for nothing

01:43:14.151 --> 01:43:16.142
and now, again,
I'm writing you a check, Mom.

01:43:16.253 --> 01:43:17.652
- Oh.
- It's ridiculous.

01:43:18.889 --> 01:43:21.084
This is $30,000 that I barely have.

01:43:21.559 --> 01:43:23.322
- But that's not enough, honey.
- Ma, I love you,

01:43:23.427 --> 01:43:25.622
but I cannot keep hemorrhaging money
for your insanity.

01:43:25.729 --> 01:43:27.390
What you need to do
is you need to go back to Henry.

01:43:27.498 --> 01:43:28.897
You need to get another job, okay?

01:43:28.999 --> 01:43:32.366
But this is my job. I have a job.
What do you... Oh, my God.

01:43:32.469 --> 01:43:34.960
- You mean like a real job with a boss?
- Yes, a real job.

01:43:35.072 --> 01:43:36.596
- I'm too old to get a...
- I'm sorry, Ma,

01:43:36.707 --> 01:43:37.765
you got to start at some point.

01:43:37.875 --> 01:43:39.866
You got to start now.
I can't keep carrying you forever.

01:43:41.278 --> 01:43:44.179
You're not the only one
who's in trouble, Ma. Please.

01:43:44.281 --> 01:43:45.205
Hello?

01:43:45.216 --> 01:43:47.611
<i>Hey, Jake.
We have a problem.</i>

01:43:49.220 --> 01:43:50.244
Go ahead.

01:43:50.354 --> 01:43:54.120
I don't know what happened.
My CFO says the money hasn't arrived yet.

01:43:56.393 --> 01:43:58.088
Yeah, but it was sent yesterday.

01:43:58.195 --> 01:44:00.823
It should have been there
before the Fedwire closed at 6:00.

01:44:01.699 --> 01:44:05.499
Well, maybe there's been some sort of mistake.
It was a large amount.

01:44:08.405 --> 01:44:09.633
Okay, just sit tight.

01:44:09.974 --> 01:44:12.374
- <i>All right?</i>
- Jesus.

01:44:19.216 --> 01:44:21.912
A few days?
In this city that's nothing.

01:44:23.053 --> 01:44:25.317
Mr. Gekko is good tenant.

01:44:25.923 --> 01:44:27.481
I appreciate it.

01:44:48.245 --> 01:44:52.477
<i>A fisherman always sees
another fisherman from afar.</i>

01:44:59.056 --> 01:45:01.957
<i>Winnie's all I got left.
You understand that?</i>

01:45:04.228 --> 01:45:05.456
<i>How much?</i>

01:45:05.663 --> 01:45:08.097
Close to $100 million by now.

01:45:10.734 --> 01:45:12.895
Don't go back in there, Jake.

01:45:16.307 --> 01:45:17.934
This is who he is.

01:45:20.711 --> 01:45:22.474
I did tell you, Jake.

01:45:23.948 --> 01:45:25.438
I did warn you.

01:45:26.951 --> 01:45:28.782
I lied to you, Winnie.

01:45:34.692 --> 01:45:38.253
I've been in contact with your father
behind your back.

01:45:42.633 --> 01:45:44.897
After we saw him at the dinner,

01:45:45.803 --> 01:45:47.964
before you gave me the money.

01:45:59.683 --> 01:46:01.048
Why?

01:46:03.787 --> 01:46:07.883
Because I thought it was the best thing
for you, you know. For us.

01:46:17.835 --> 01:46:19.063
I just wanted to...

01:46:26.577 --> 01:46:28.135
You're like him.

01:46:30.314 --> 01:46:32.349
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Winnie.

01:46:35.386 --> 01:46:38.378
I'll make it up to you.
I promise I'll get the money back.

01:46:38.622 --> 01:46:42.683
I don't care about the money, Jake!
This is not about the money.

01:46:42.793 --> 01:46:45.523
This is about you and me,
and we are not good anymore.

01:46:48.432 --> 01:46:50.866
Winn, we are good.
Come on.

01:46:52.269 --> 01:46:53.258
We are good.

01:46:54.138 --> 01:46:56.368
- Come on, Winn. We're good.
- No.

01:46:59.209 --> 01:47:02.076
We're supposed to make
each other feel safe.

01:47:04.081 --> 01:47:06.174
Otherwise, what's the point?

01:47:12.356 --> 01:47:13.914
It's gone, Jake.

01:47:15.125 --> 01:47:17.093
It's not. Please don't.

01:47:17.194 --> 01:47:18.627
Take it.

01:47:25.069 --> 01:47:26.536
Come on, Winn.

01:47:27.805 --> 01:47:29.102
Please go.

01:47:30.441 --> 01:47:31.601
Please.

01:47:32.810 --> 01:47:33.799
Go.

01:47:40.818 --> 01:47:42.115
I'm sorry.

01:48:15.219 --> 01:48:20.282
China, India, Brazil.
Silver, oil, copper, I want to own it all.

01:48:20.524 --> 01:48:23.015
Buy me Churchill Schwartz,

01:48:23.127 --> 01:48:25.618
and get me updates
on the other financials.

01:48:25.729 --> 01:48:28.493
I'm looking for deals.
Only good deals.

01:48:28.599 --> 01:48:32.000
Just ride the trends.
Just don't try too hard for the turns.

01:48:32.102 --> 01:48:34.195
It's just like the old days, Bobby.

01:48:34.304 --> 01:48:36.329
<i>What do you feel
about California municipals, Gordon?</i>

01:48:36.440 --> 01:48:39.034
No way.
California has made more mistakes

01:48:39.143 --> 01:48:41.771
than Yogi Berra reciting Shakespeare.

01:48:43.080 --> 01:48:46.208
Right now, it is ugly times ugly.

01:48:47.117 --> 01:48:49.585
And that's when the ugly get going.

01:48:50.687 --> 01:48:54.088
You tell them for me, babe,
Gordon Gekko is back.

01:48:56.960 --> 01:49:00.259
I'm looking for distressed securities.
I'm trying to get a hold of them

01:49:00.364 --> 01:49:03.060
before the government does.
You got that?

01:49:03.800 --> 01:49:04.926
Okay.

01:49:05.636 --> 01:49:08.230
- Here you are, Mr. Gekko.
- Nice, Harry.

01:49:08.705 --> 01:49:11.674
Well, then, Alex,
you tell the Treasury Department for me

01:49:11.775 --> 01:49:15.006
that I'm willing to stand
on the other side of their auction.

01:49:15.112 --> 01:49:17.603
Not too tight under the arms, Mr. Gekko?

01:49:17.714 --> 01:49:20.774
Jesus Christ. I tell you,
the government's worse than a wife.

01:49:20.884 --> 01:49:23.910
They got all the power,
they got half the money.

01:49:24.021 --> 01:49:26.455
Now they're working
on getting the other half.

01:49:26.823 --> 01:49:28.552
Hey, hey, stay positive, pal.

01:49:28.659 --> 01:49:31.423
Most people, they lose,
they whine and quit.

01:49:31.528 --> 01:49:32.927
But you got to be there for the turns.

01:49:33.030 --> 01:49:35.464
Everybody's got good luck,
everybody's got bad luck.

01:49:35.566 --> 01:49:39.127
Don't run when you lose.
Don't whine when it hurts.

01:49:39.236 --> 01:49:41.204
It's like the first grade, Jerry.

01:49:41.305 --> 01:49:43.000
Nobody likes a crybaby.

01:49:43.106 --> 01:49:45.904
- Whooshing sound.
- I'll take four of these.

01:49:59.590 --> 01:50:01.751
Feels good to be back on top, huh?

01:50:05.862 --> 01:50:08.592
Hey, champ.
What brings you to London?

01:50:08.799 --> 01:50:10.790
You, Gordo.

01:50:12.936 --> 01:50:15.234
You want to make one last trade?

01:50:15.339 --> 01:50:17.330
Well, that depends.

01:50:18.909 --> 01:50:21.241
Did you ever really want
to reconcile with her?

01:50:23.280 --> 01:50:24.645
I'm human.

01:50:24.748 --> 01:50:26.113
Then why did you do it?

01:50:26.216 --> 01:50:28.047
Well, it's the same answer.

01:50:28.151 --> 01:50:31.143
Look, I told you before,
Winnie was gonna stake me when I got out.

01:50:31.722 --> 01:50:34.054
- You remember, she reneged.
- Sure, she did.

01:50:34.691 --> 01:50:37.057
It makes you feel better
about stealing from your own blood,

01:50:37.294 --> 01:50:38.591
doesn't it?

01:50:38.695 --> 01:50:40.686
Every thief has some excuse.

01:50:41.064 --> 01:50:43.555
Hey, don't you act so superior, kid.

01:50:44.701 --> 01:50:49.661
They took 122 thousand hours of my life
for a victimless crime.

01:50:49.873 --> 01:50:52.569
I ate my bitterness every goddamn day.

01:50:52.676 --> 01:50:54.337
And when I got out,
who was waiting for me?

01:50:54.444 --> 01:50:55.604
Nobody!

01:50:56.580 --> 01:50:58.548
Not even my own daughter.

01:50:59.383 --> 01:51:02.284
I thought Bretton was slime
until I met you.

01:51:03.153 --> 01:51:05.678
I just never believed that a man
would sell out his own daughter.

01:51:05.789 --> 01:51:09.020
You die your way, I'll die mine.
Get the hell out of here.

01:51:09.126 --> 01:51:10.252
You know, she left me, Gordon.

01:51:10.527 --> 01:51:11.585
Yeah?

01:51:13.063 --> 01:51:15.156
I'm sorry about that.

01:51:15.265 --> 01:51:17.324
Yeah? I bet you are.

01:51:18.068 --> 01:51:20.036
You left it all in ruins.

01:51:21.505 --> 01:51:25.305
But no matter how much money you make,
you'll never be rich.

01:51:25.409 --> 01:51:29.209
See, that's what you never got, kid.
It's not about the money.

01:51:30.314 --> 01:51:33.715
It's about the game.
The game between people.

01:51:34.751 --> 01:51:36.514
And that's all it is.

01:51:39.089 --> 01:51:40.420
Speaking of,

01:51:42.125 --> 01:51:43.888
what's the trade?

01:51:44.094 --> 01:51:48.326
You give back the principal to Winnie.
The $100 million.

01:51:50.567 --> 01:51:52.660
And what do I get in return?

01:51:55.739 --> 01:51:57.104
Put this in.

01:52:14.725 --> 01:52:16.488
That's your grandson.

01:52:34.077 --> 01:52:37.569
You said, "The most valuable commodity
I know is time."

01:52:38.749 --> 01:52:40.614
You're looking at time.

01:52:41.351 --> 01:52:42.613
Not money.

01:52:45.622 --> 01:52:47.385
This is time, Gordon.

01:53:00.337 --> 01:53:04.569
I'm sorry, Jake, but this is simply
a trade I cannot make.

01:53:17.687 --> 01:53:19.814
You're a sad man, Gordon.

01:54:34.197 --> 01:54:35.687
You really want to get
this site on the map?

01:54:35.799 --> 01:54:39.462
You break this story.
It'll take some time, but it'll spread.

01:54:39.569 --> 01:54:42.163
It's the single greatest transfer of wealth
in American history

01:54:42.272 --> 01:54:44.604
from Main Street to Wall Street,
and it's all true.

01:54:44.708 --> 01:54:47.677
And it will happen again because
people like you and me want to be lied to.

01:54:48.378 --> 01:54:50.312
We like bedtime stories.

01:54:53.450 --> 01:54:57.045
I miss you like crazy,
and I love you, baby, and I'm sorry.

01:55:41.464 --> 01:55:46.458
Bretton James, the rumor is that
he was shorting Keller Zabel stock

01:55:46.570 --> 01:55:48.060
before he ended up acquiring it.

01:55:48.371 --> 01:55:50.839
Why would he do that?
This is the rock star of Wall Street.

01:55:50.941 --> 01:55:51.965
Did you hear about Bretton James?

01:55:52.142 --> 01:55:55.168
CNBC will say he's hedging,
but if you ask me it's a fraud.

01:55:55.378 --> 01:55:58.779
It's a tiny website. Who cares?

01:55:59.215 --> 01:56:02.207
Gekko's daughter
and that smartass kid I fired, Moore.

01:56:02.319 --> 01:56:05.618
What is this about the rumor that led
to Louis Zabel committing suicide?

01:56:05.722 --> 01:56:08.748
Well, shorting his own company,
you can't bust him for that.

01:56:08.858 --> 01:56:12.316
But they can get him for running
false rumors on Zabel, that's serious.

01:56:12.429 --> 01:56:14.192
It's gone viral, Bretton.

01:56:14.297 --> 01:56:17.061
Bloomberg has a summary out on it.
Reuters is playing the story big.

01:56:17.167 --> 01:56:20.261
It's become legitimate.
Congress is next.

01:56:21.571 --> 01:56:23.664
This bank is bigger than you, Bretton.

01:56:24.541 --> 01:56:27.305
We know there's nothing illegal here, Jimmy.

01:56:28.278 --> 01:56:29.336
Jack?

01:56:32.882 --> 01:56:33.974
Julie...

01:56:35.251 --> 01:56:37.048
Are you stupid or what?

01:56:37.387 --> 01:56:39.981
Trading for your account in your position?

01:56:40.624 --> 01:56:44.060
You pigged out, kid.
You were making a fortune here.

01:56:44.327 --> 01:56:46.625
What the hell is wrong with you?

01:56:47.597 --> 01:56:48.791
Come on.

01:56:50.700 --> 01:56:52.395
So I double-dipped.

01:56:52.769 --> 01:56:53.997
Who hasn't?

01:56:54.104 --> 01:56:57.267
Now, in your time,
you must have done some things.

01:56:58.074 --> 01:56:59.939
You're retiring, Julie.

01:57:00.910 --> 01:57:03.003
Why don't you step up in front of this?

01:57:03.346 --> 01:57:04.938
You can afford it.

01:57:05.048 --> 01:57:06.811
I can still run this place

01:57:06.916 --> 01:57:10.909
and make you more money
than you ever dreamed.

01:57:13.690 --> 01:57:17.626
We both know that's not
going to happen, kid.

01:57:26.636 --> 01:57:27.762
Julie.

01:57:28.505 --> 01:57:30.564
Think about this, please.

01:57:30.674 --> 01:57:32.198
You look for the birds.

01:57:33.710 --> 01:57:36.270
They're going to help you, those birds.
You'll see. Good luck.

01:57:41.351 --> 01:57:45.947
<i>I think I waited too long</i>

01:57:47.323 --> 01:57:52.158
<i>I'm moving into the dollhouse</i>

01:57:52.796 --> 01:57:55.458
<i>Some days we exercise</i>

01:57:55.565 --> 01:57:58.295
<i>Some days we harmonize</i>

01:57:58.401 --> 01:58:03.464
<i>Look away, look away
Look away, oh, yeah</i>

01:58:06.342 --> 01:58:09.277
I don't wanna sound like a rooster
taking credit for the dawn,

01:58:09.379 --> 01:58:13.475
but turning $100 million into $1.1 billion

01:58:13.583 --> 01:58:16.347
in this market,
takes some brains, right?

01:58:17.287 --> 01:58:19.346
My guys are good.

01:58:20.490 --> 01:58:23.721
And it's no wonder our new fund
is over-subscribed.

01:58:24.661 --> 01:58:28.290
But for you,
I'm gonna initiate a third fund.

01:58:29.599 --> 01:58:33.467
Because, frankly, Julie,
I couldn't be more excited about this.

01:58:33.570 --> 01:58:36.698
To finally be in business
with you and your firm.

01:58:39.442 --> 01:58:41.933
And us with you, Gekko.

01:58:48.051 --> 01:58:49.018
Yeah.

01:58:51.321 --> 01:58:53.755
<i>What is the definition of insanity?</i>

01:58:55.191 --> 01:58:59.594
<i>It's doing the same thing over and over
and expecting a different result.</i>

01:59:01.965 --> 01:59:04.991
<i>By that standard,
most of us are insane.</i>

01:59:05.101 --> 01:59:07.069
<i>But not at the same time.</i>

01:59:08.371 --> 01:59:10.430
<i>And on that basis we trust.</i>

01:59:12.242 --> 01:59:13.937
<i>But can this way of life endure</i>

01:59:14.043 --> 01:59:17.308
<i>if more and more people are insane
at the same time?</i>

01:59:19.015 --> 01:59:22.712
<i>It becomes, as Gordon said,
"Systemic."</i>

01:59:23.386 --> 01:59:24.478
<i>Like cancer.</i>

01:59:27.123 --> 01:59:28.750
<i>What happens then?</i>

01:59:31.127 --> 01:59:32.992
<i>Like I said,</i>

01:59:33.096 --> 01:59:36.429
<i>the mother of all bubbles
was the Cambrian Explosion.</i>

01:59:37.834 --> 01:59:40.735
<i>And it happened by chance
over 500 million years ago.</i>

01:59:40.837 --> 01:59:42.065
Louis Zabel, Bretton?

01:59:42.172 --> 01:59:43.332
Tell us about Louis Zabel.

01:59:44.174 --> 01:59:46.836
- Come on. Come on.
- No!

01:59:48.645 --> 01:59:51.773
<i>Scientists will tell you
it was unprecedented,</i>

01:59:51.881 --> 01:59:53.178
<i>it happened in a flash.</i>

01:59:56.186 --> 01:59:57.847
<i>And from it,</i>

01:59:57.954 --> 02:00:01.515
<i>suddenly the world
had millions of new species.</i>

02:00:01.624 --> 02:00:03.819
I'd love a coffee.
So be in, like, 10.

02:00:03.927 --> 02:00:05.622
- <i>And from that...</i>
- Where are you going?

02:00:05.728 --> 02:00:06.956
<i>was born us.</i>

02:00:07.063 --> 02:00:08.052
Look at you!

02:00:08.164 --> 02:00:09.153
<i>The human race.</i>

02:00:09.265 --> 02:00:11.995
Mr. Schwartz, I hear you are leaving us.

02:00:12.202 --> 02:00:14.397
No, that won't be soon enough.

02:00:14.504 --> 02:00:16.369
Oh. Have you thought
about a timeshare in Florida?

02:00:16.472 --> 02:00:17.962
I could hook you up in Boca.

02:00:19.108 --> 02:00:20.837
Sit down, Mr. James.

02:00:21.644 --> 02:00:25.774
<i>Now, in that sense,
bubbles are evolutionary.</i>

02:00:25.982 --> 02:00:28.041
This is only a preliminary proceeding.

02:00:28.151 --> 02:00:29.982
But I want you to know
you're under investigation

02:00:30.086 --> 02:00:33.681
on accusations of tax evasion
and stock manipulation

02:00:33.790 --> 02:00:37.658
through, among others,
an entity called Locust Fund.

02:00:37.760 --> 02:00:40.923
Although, I want to first get
to the matter of Louis Zabel.

02:00:41.030 --> 02:00:43.260
I see here that you cooperated
with this office

02:00:43.366 --> 02:00:46.358
and with the federal authorities in 1988

02:00:46.469 --> 02:00:49.927
when the investigations
of one Gordon Gekko began.

02:00:50.039 --> 02:00:51.631
<i>They kill excess.</i>

02:00:52.709 --> 02:00:54.574
<i>They lean out the herd.</i>

02:00:55.311 --> 02:00:57.006
<i>But they never die.</i>

02:00:58.147 --> 02:01:00.513
<i>They just come back
in different forms.</i>

02:01:10.226 --> 02:01:12.126
<i>When they burst,</i>

02:01:12.228 --> 02:01:14.389
<i>they give birth to a new day.</i>

02:01:29.112 --> 02:01:30.977
<i>Always creating change.</i>

02:01:51.701 --> 02:01:53.293
Can I carry that?

02:01:58.408 --> 02:02:00.467
You're not sleeping either?

02:02:00.910 --> 02:02:02.878
He woke me up last night.

02:02:06.683 --> 02:02:07.741
Yeah.

02:02:08.518 --> 02:02:09.644
Can I?

02:02:10.820 --> 02:02:11.980
Yeah.

02:02:23.232 --> 02:02:24.358
There?

02:02:25.034 --> 02:02:26.092
Yeah.

02:02:33.676 --> 02:02:36.042
I just got off the phone with Dr. Masters.

02:02:36.145 --> 02:02:37.510
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

02:02:38.481 --> 02:02:39.971
Very happy man.

02:02:40.683 --> 02:02:42.878
Renewed interests from investors.

02:02:43.019 --> 02:02:44.850
Because of your story.

02:02:45.455 --> 02:02:46.922
So, thank you.

02:02:51.294 --> 02:02:52.989
I miss you, Winnie.

02:02:54.497 --> 02:02:55.828
I miss you.

02:02:58.835 --> 02:03:00.996
I don't know how to fix this.

02:03:02.805 --> 02:03:04.238
Neither do I.

02:03:06.743 --> 02:03:08.370
It's different now.

02:03:08.478 --> 02:03:11.072
- What can I do? I mean, I...
- Nothing.

02:03:13.049 --> 02:03:14.243
Nothing.

02:03:24.260 --> 02:03:25.318
Thank you.

02:03:26.162 --> 02:03:28.096
- Good night.
- Good night.

02:03:33.369 --> 02:03:35.303
Where are you two going?

02:03:47.550 --> 02:03:50.576
What, nobody around here
believes in comebacks?

02:03:56.426 --> 02:03:58.417
Winn, I owe you something.

02:03:59.929 --> 02:04:02.591
I don't want it.
I never did.

02:04:03.966 --> 02:04:05.524
No, I figured that.

02:04:05.635 --> 02:04:09.537
But, you know,
when choosing between two evils,

02:04:09.639 --> 02:04:14.440
I like to try the one
that I haven't tried before.

02:04:16.279 --> 02:04:20.079
So I deposited a check of $100 million

02:04:21.417 --> 02:04:23.977
made out to United Fusion.

02:04:27.356 --> 02:04:30.587
From some offshore fund
no one needs to know about.

02:04:32.161 --> 02:04:35.187
Wouldn't you say green
is the new bubble, Jake?

02:04:44.774 --> 02:04:46.833
You two make a nice couple.

02:04:54.650 --> 02:04:58.177
You know, Winn, human beings,

02:05:00.690 --> 02:05:02.783
we got to give them a break.

02:05:04.927 --> 02:05:06.656
We're all mixed bags.

02:05:13.803 --> 02:05:14.792
But

02:05:16.706 --> 02:05:18.264
my grandson,

02:05:20.009 --> 02:05:21.306
and you...

02:05:23.613 --> 02:05:26.912
And maybe, you know,
you'll let me be a father again.

02:05:43.032 --> 02:05:48.868
<i>The dimming of the light
makes the picture clearer</i>

02:05:49.338 --> 02:05:52.739
<i>It's just an old photograph</i>

02:05:52.842 --> 02:05:56.801
<i>There's nothing to hide</i>

02:05:56.913 --> 02:06:02.510
<i>And we'll mix our lives together</i>

02:06:04.787 --> 02:06:07.585
<i>Every hand</i>

02:06:07.857 --> 02:06:14.592
<i>Goes searching for its partner</i>

02:06:16.465 --> 02:06:19.093
<i>In crime</i>

02:06:19.202 --> 02:06:21.670
<i>Connecting</i>

02:06:22.471 --> 02:06:26.430
<i>To every living soul</i>

02:06:29.312 --> 02:06:31.075
<i>I'm looking for a home</i>

02:06:32.715 --> 02:06:36.583
<i>Where the wheels are turning</i>

02:06:36.686 --> 02:06:41.885
<i>Home
Why I keep returning</i>

02:06:42.191 --> 02:06:48.562
<i>Home
Will infect what ever you do</i>

02:06:53.502 --> 02:06:58.872
<i>Home
With the neighbors fighting</i>

02:06:59.108 --> 02:07:04.512
